The paper discusses error correction and information theory concepts related to fountain codes, which are commonly used in communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential for attacks on the system, which falls under the scope of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of fountain codes in broadcasting and storage systems suggests that it could also fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the statistical behavior of sequential decoding, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
